<p>Since the dataset was too sparse and noisy to fit a spatiotemporal model, the monthly counts of CHIKV- and ZIKV-infected cases were aggregated to consider only the potential spatial variation of the infection over the entire study period. A standardised incidence rate (SIR) for each neighbourhood was calculated taking the distribution of cases and population into account, as follows: 
 <disp-formula>
  <math id="mm1">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mi>S</mi>
     <mi>I</mi>
     <msub>
      <mi>R</mi>
      <mi>i</mi>
     </msub>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mfrac>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mi>O</mi>
        <mi>i</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mi>E</mi>
        <mi>i</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </mfrac>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm2">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>O</mi>
      <mi>i</mi>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is the observed number of cases, 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm3">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>E</mi>
      <mi>i</mi>
     </msub>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mi>r</mi>
     <msub>
      <mi>P</mi>
      <mi>i</mi>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is the expected number of cases, 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm4">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>P</mi>
      <mi>i</mi>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is the population and 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm5">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mi>r</mi>
     <mo>=</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm6">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mfrac>
      <mrow>
       <msubsup>
        <mstyle mathsize="100%" displaystyle="true">
         <mo>∑</mo>
        </mstyle>
        <mrow>
         <mi>i</mi>
         <mo>=</mo>
         <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
        <mi>n</mi>
       </msubsup>
       <msub>
        <mi>O</mi>
        <mi>i</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mrow>
       <msubsup>
        <mstyle mathsize="100%" displaystyle="true">
         <mo>∑</mo>
        </mstyle>
        <mrow>
         <mi>i</mi>
         <mo>=</mo>
         <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
        <mi>n</mi>
       </msubsup>
       <msub>
        <mi>P</mi>
        <mi>i</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </mfrac>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is the overall incidence ratio.
</p>
